== Mashed Potato ==

Boil a large #pot{} of salted @water{to taste} for the @potatoes{3}.

Chop the potatoes into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pan{} off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste} and a splash of @?milk{to taste} or water. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

== Meatballs ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated).

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

In a large #bowl{}, mix the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, 2 tbsp water and ½ tsp salt (double both for 4p).

Add the @Irish Beef Mince{250%g} and half the @Italian Herbs{½%sachet} (double for 4p).

Season with @pepper{to taste} and mix together by hand.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, five per person. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the beef meatballs until browned all over and cooked through, shifting frequently, ~{10-12%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

== Spinach Sauce ==

Return the pan to medium-high heat, with a drizzle of oil if needed.

Fry the @onion{1}(peeled, halved and chopped) and @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Beef Stock{1%sachet}(stock powder), @Passata{1%pack}, @Worcester Sauce{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and 50ml water (double both for 4p). Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in the @Baby Spinach{60%g}(stems removed) and half the parsley. Add the meatballs and cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Stir through a knob of @butter{to taste}.

== To Serve ==

Divide the creamy mashed potato between #bowls{}.

Top with meatballs and spinach sauce.

Garnish with a sprinkling of the remaining parsley.